					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the first half of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>420 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>230</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>120</height>
										<width>90</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>420 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Maniculae, e.g., folio 8r, 111v, 259r.</p>
									<p>Diagrams in black and red ink, folio 118r, 118v, 119v.</p>
									<p>Initial words and headings given in larger square characters, partly in red ink.</p>
									<p>Additions and corrections given often in the margin.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Sefardi semi-cursive of the 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yitsḥaḳ ben Mosheh ben Zeraḥ </name> of <name type="place">Segovia</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 420v. </summary>
